      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Imagine an energy ladder with the exact ground energy at the floor. Trial-state energies can descend as the guess improves, but no valid trial expectation value crosses that floor.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "collapse"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.01,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:54:58"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "Why should a wrong wave function make an error in only one direction? What prevents a clever but inaccurate guess from producing an energy that is too low?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.38,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B03.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:54:58"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Expand the trial state in the exact energy eigenstates. Each coefficient says how much of one eigenstate the trial contains, and normalization makes the squared coefficients add to one.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "decompose"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.46,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:54:58"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The expected energy becomes the sum of each exact energy times its nonnegative probability weight. It is literally a weighted average of the spectrum.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "average"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.19,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:54:58"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "estimated_duration_s": 5,
      "narration_text": "And every weighted average is at least its smallest entry.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 3.73,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:54:58"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Subtract the ground energy. The difference is a sum of probability weights times E n minus E zero. Every factor is nonnegative, so the entire difference cannot be negative.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "derive"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.41,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B07.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:54:58"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "Equality occurs only when the trial state has support entirely inside the ground-energy eigenspace. Any excited-state component pushes the average upward.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "lift"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.83,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B08.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:54:58"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "For helium, try two hydrogen-like orbitals with one adjustable effective nuclear charge Z star. The trial family is imperfect, but its energy can be minimized over that one parameter.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "scan"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.37,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B09.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:54:58"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "For this simple product trial, the energy in Hartrees is Z star squared minus twenty-seven eighths Z star. The parabola reaches its minimum at Z star equals twenty-seven sixteenths, or 1.6875.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "minimize"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 13.59,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B10.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:54:58"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "With Z star equal two, the estimate is minus 74.83 electron volts. Optimizing gives minus 77.49. The exact nonrelativistic ground energy is about minus 79.01. Both guesses remain higher, meaning less negative.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 15.85,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B11.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T14:54:58"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "Optimization tightens the ceiling; it does not move the floor. Better trial families can approach the exact ground energy from above.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "collapse"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.06,
